Zindella has recently come out of the void that is between life and death. Formerly a half-elf bard, she must struggle with the huge body of a barbarian girl, and the  inability to sing. Without the production of music coming from  her voice, Zindella wonders why she was sent back to be a champion when she cannot do the things she could  to make things right with Norrath. Coming soon: Zindella's first encounter with the servants of Cazic-Thule, the god who imprisoned her for so long.<br>
