But he let me come along after that, so long as I kept away from tae polar bears, when tae others moved in fer tae kill.  Da learned fast that I was good at finding tae polar bear cubs, which have tae best hides.  I could almost smell tae wee things.  I think it was tae first glimmers of my magic coming through.<br>
<br>
I was ten summers old when tae ice goblins came.  I woke up in tae night tae find tae house on fire, and I ran, so I did.  Jamie bundled me out of tae window and yelled at me tae hide in tae canyons.  I ran and ran and hid in a snowdrift until tae morning came.  I'd nae been so cold in all my life.  When I got back tae the house, all there was were blackened stone and smouldering thatch.<br>
<br>
People from tae McRothe clan, our neighbours, came and found me picking through the rubble.  They'd seen tae fire in tae night and had come over tae see what was going on.  I said that I couldnae find my Da and me brothers.  They looked but they could nae find them either.  Tae goblins must have taken them and ye all know what happens tae people who get taken by goblins.<br>
<br>
Da had no brothers or sisters and so I had nae family or clan tae look after me.  Tae McRothes gave me tae the Shamans in Halas, as they didnae want another mouth tae feed.  I think they thought I was too small, or summin, tae be of use tae them.<br>
<br>
I didnae like my time in Halas.  The shamans are fair strict in their instruction.  My magic blossomed and grew and I was pleased with myself, but they always had more fer me tae do.  Old Heather McPherson, who was supposed  tae instruct me, called me arrogant and puffed up with pride and many's tae time I had tae scrub tae floor or wash out tae pots because she didnae like summin I did.<br>
<br>
Tae taught me tae read, taught me of tae Tribunal and their laws and a little of fighting.  I enjoyed tae fighting.  I reckon I'd be a better warrior than shaman, maybe, but magics a great thing tae be sure.  Tae spirits of tae land talk to ye and tae very wind and ice of tae Everfrost ye can bend tae your command !<br>
<br>
As soon as I reached my eighteenth summer and tae Shamans would let me go, I left Halas.  Now I'm wandering about Norrath, as a journeywoman shamaness, seeking adventure.  Heather McPherson told me nae good would come of this and I'd better stay in Halas instead, but what does that dried up stay at home know of anything ?<br>
